It did not appeal to me. Teachers, examples, material, presentation. One of the early examples, that banks "owned" your data and were not willing to pass them on to their competitors, for free presumably, just seemed nonsense. A nice political statement, banks are bad, but also ignoring that you are the ultimate owner of your data, there is nothing the bank has about you on original data, that you do not have. If you do not, it just shows you are irresponsible regarding your own information.

I have completed all the quiz and assignments in the course, I have even submitted the final project. As I started the course late I dont see any peers to review my project or me to review their project I'm not able to complete my course and get the subscription.

This course looks more like a podcast. This course seems recorded around 2017 and is not helpful five years later. I wouldn't say I liked the final project because it was based on peer review. When analyzing myself at the end of this course, I believe that I have wasted more time than I have gained knowledge.

T​he peer-graded assignment was the best part - until I had to rate others.
It was a huge burden to rate my peers' work, because I had to tell some of them, that "copy-pasting" the entire essay from a webpage is not a good solution. I still feel bad about this, because it does not feel good to give bad grades, and tell someone, that the submitted solution is not acceptable, because 0 energy was invested into it. This shouldn't be our job.
I can only hope, that no one receives a certificate without putting enough work into the assignment.
